My brothers of choice,<br><br>
On line with SW! I have a few thoughts I would like to<br>
share based upon my personal experience.<br><br>
In the past two years, I have grappled with many similar<br>
dilemmas. Just what is this stuff PTSD, the thing in my<br>
head given a name by those far more familiar with its<br>
objective realities than I.<br><br>
I think my first brush at the core of it all ocurred with a<br>
fast elevator ride to the bottom. Not the kind of bottom of<br>
a crisis, but to the bottom of my mind. What I found there<br>
was both frightening and fascinating at the same time.<br><br>
Karl Jung refers to the architypical human, that core<br>
reality of behavior underpinning the layers of<br>
socialization, humanization, or civilization of that which<br>
we like to realize as ourselves in the ideal sense, the<br>
basal human being not modified by social conditions.<br><br>
Fright, fight, flight. Interesting thought upon which to <br>
expand.<br><br>
I am beginning to acquire skills which enables me to look at<br>
myself on the way down. As I move downward, I see inhibitons<br>
move aside, and rules, other than those that suit me, are<br>
not as functional as they should be in the eyes of others.<br><br>
These areas are those I am exploring in my own way of<br>
dealing with this thing in my head, my old friend,<br>
companion, PTSD, the gift that keeps on giving.<br><br>
